Petition of prestigious universities from Iasi and the country
More than 200 researchers, academics, personalities and students from the country have signed a petition launched by the Academic Society of Romania in which they request the Ministry of Education and Scientific Research to evaluate, sanction and even abolish doctoral schools in Romania "which allow and promote academic imposture".
Signers of the petition launched on September 10 include teachers and teachers from Iași.
Among the university signatories of the petition in the Iași academic environment is, for example, Prof.Dr. Liviu Antonesei.
At the national level, the petition has names from former Education Ministers, such as Mircea Miclea, to people of culture who are also academic staff, such as Andrei Pleşu, Aurora Liiceanu or Alina Mungiu-Pippidi.
"Although the Education Act provides for the evaluation of doctoral schools, this has not been achieved so far, thus prompting the lack of concrete sanctions for doctoral schools that blatantly violate ethical norms in scientific research and do not produce relevant and internationally recognized performance," the petition reads.
The petition specifically requires compliance with the Law of National Education, evaluation of doctoral schools, suspension of the right of operation for any doctoral school where more than two plagiarisms have been found, until the assessment and remedy of the situation.
The last requirement is the suspension of the right of operation for any doctoral school where there is no minimum number of doctoral leaders provided by law meeting the criteria imposed by the National Council of Scientific Research in 2011 for eligibility to IDEI-type project grants.
Do you respect less a general without a doctorate, or a politician, or an intelligence agent in the Middle East?
"Why don't there be other academies in Europe that give PhDs organized by secret services, and top military people who give their doctorate do it at autonomous academic institutions, where quality is verified by the academic environment?" said Alina Mungiu-Pippidi, president of the Romanian Academic Society, initiator of the petition, also originating in Iasi.
This can be completed by all the wishers on the Society's website, and the final signatures will be submitted by the organization to the Ministry of Education and Scientific Research.
