Winner in the Iași Rally, Simone Tempestini secured his national title at the rally, becoming the youngest winner in championship history
The 2015 Iasului Cotnari rally ended with a fabulous result of the young pilot Simone Tempestini, Italian with Romanian citizenship, who at 21 years old won all nine special challenges of the most difficult stage in the National Rally Championship.
Still leading the competition, Simone became one stage ahead of the final, national champion, with co-pilot Dorin Pulpea on a Ford Fiesta R5.
Tempestini juniori became the youngest Romanian rally champion, the previous recordman, since 2011, belonging to Valentin Porcișteanu (28 years and nine months).
In the seven stages of the Dunlop National Rally Championship, Simone won 47 special challenges, and the performance from Iași reissues the previous one, from the Arad Rally.
